## Version scheme: semver with pre-release suffixes

MYCELIUM_VERSION in mycelium.sh line 4 is the single source of truth.
mycelium.sh --version reads it. The installer prints it after install.

### Format
  MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH            — stable release on main (tagged)
  MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH-rc.N       — release candidate on a feature branch
  MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH-<branch>.N — experimental pre-release

### Rules
1. main always has a clean semver (no suffix). Example: 0.1.0
2. Feature branches bump MINOR and add a suffix. Example: 0.2.0-rc.1
3. Every push to main must have a matching git tag: v0.1.0, v0.2.0, etc.
4. Tags are immutable. Never delete or move a tag.
5. The version string in mycelium.sh must match the git tag at that commit.
6. When a feature branch merges to main, the suffix is removed: 0.2.0-rc.1 → 0.2.0
7. Bump rc.N on the feature branch when making significant changes during testing.

### Enforcement
- The pre-commit hook should verify MYCELIUM_VERSION is present and well-formed.
- CI should verify the version string matches the git tag (on tagged commits).
- Agents: always check mycelium.sh --version before starting work. If it says -rc or
  -branch, you are NOT on stable main.

### Current versions
  v0.1.0       — core single-repo (main, tagged, pushed)
  0.2.0-rc.1   — multi-repo export/import (multi-repo branch, local)

### Install pinning
  VERSION=0.1.0 curl -fsSL .../install.sh | bash   # specific version
  curl -fsSL .../install.sh | bash                   # latest main
